48:36.706 --> 48:38.416
Hmm.

48:38.458 --> 48:41.336
Okay, this telethon's
actually gone on so long

48:41.377 --> 48:44.255
we're raising money for
the cameramen's arthritis now.

48:44.297 --> 48:46.549
-(mouthing)
-And now the stage manager's

48:46.591 --> 48:48.092
going like this.

48:48.134 --> 48:50.470
We all know what that means
in show business.

48:50.511 --> 48:52.388
-Whoopee!
-(cheering and applause)

48:52.430 --> 48:53.973
It's whoopee time, everybody.

48:54.015 --> 48:55.308
Everybody make whoopee.

48:55.350 --> 48:56.809
(cheering, whistling)

48:56.851 --> 48:59.187
No, actually, I think
they want me to wrap it up.

48:59.228 --> 49:01.522
Thank you for watching,
everybody.

49:01.564 --> 49:03.941
I'm Mrs. Maisel.
Thank you for giving.

49:03.983 --> 49:06.277
Good night.

49:06.319 --> 49:07.904
(cheering and applause)

49:07.945 --> 49:09.906
Mrs. Maisel, everyone!
That was wonderful.

49:09.947 --> 49:12.325
-Thank you.
-Just wonderful.

49:12.367 --> 49:14.952
Who knew there were people
who were still up?

49:14.994 --> 49:17.705
We've never had
this many calls so late.

49:17.747 --> 49:20.458
We'll keep our phones manned,
so keep calling.

49:20.500 --> 49:22.877
And thank you and...

49:22.919 --> 49:25.922
tune in next year
for our fourth annual

49:25.963 --> 49:28.591
Stop Arthritis
and Rheumatism Telethon.

49:28.633 --> 49:30.009
Good night.

49:30.051 --> 49:32.470
(cheering and applause)

49:34.097 --> 49:35.306
Let's call it a day, guys.

49:35.348 --> 49:36.891
-Bye, Susie.
-See ya, Irene.

49:36.933 --> 49:38.893
Hope my wife stayed up for that.
She'd love it.

49:38.935 --> 49:41.229
-Nice job, guys.
-Make her stick to the script
next time?

49:41.270 --> 49:43.481
-Never.
-Long day.

49:43.523 --> 49:45.483
